import warnings

from selenium import webdriver
from bs4 import BeautifulSoup


dataset_text = []
dataset_target = []

for j in ["","",""]: 
    for i in range(2,22):
        url = "https://www.anekdot.ru/tags/" + j+ "/"+str(i)


        driver = webdriver.Chrome(r"C:\Users\m.teplov\Downloads\chromedriver_win32 (1)\chromedriver.exe")
        driver.implicitly_wait(30)
        driver.get(url)
        soup_level1=BeautifulSoup(driver.page_source)

        for hit in soup_level1.findAll(attrs={'class' : 'topicbox'}):
            for i in hit.findAll(attrs={'class' : 'text'}):
                dataset_text.append(i.getText())
                dataset_target.append(j)

        driver.close()

def f_tokenizer(s):#  :        ,
    b = pd.read_excel('stop_words.xlsx')#   ,     , ,  
    stop_words = [b['stop_words'][q] for q in range(0,b.shape[0])]
    morph = pymorphy2.MorphAnalyzer()
    f = []
    punct = ['.',',',' ','"','!','(',')','?','+', '*', '-',':', ';', '?', '[', ']', '_','#','/']
    for r in punct:
        s = s.replace(r,' ')
    words = s.split(' ')
    for word in words:
        m = morph.parse(word)
        word = m[0]
        if word.tag.POS   in ('NOUN','ADJF'):#         ,
             if word.normal_form not in stop_words:#         
                        f.append(word.normal_form+'_'+word.tag.POS)
    return(f)

def plot_confusion_matrix(cm, title='Confusion matrix', cmap=plt.cm.Blues):
    plt.imshow(cm, interpolation='nearest', cmap=cmap, vmin=0, vmax=1)
    plt.title(title)
    plt.colorbar()
    plt.clim(0, 1);
    tick_marks = np.arange(len(lenght))
    target_names = lenght
    plt.xticks(tick_marks, target_names, rotation=90)
    plt.yticks(tick_marks, target_names)
    plt.tight_layout()
    plt.ylabel('True label')
    plt.xlabel('Predicted label')
    plt.show()
    
    
    
def evaluate_prediction(predictions, target, title="Confusion matrix"):
    print('accuracy %s' % accuracy_score(target, predictions))
    cm = confusion_matrix(target, predictions)
    print('confusion matrix\n %s' % cm)
    print('(row=expected, col=predicted)')
    
    cm_normalized = cm.astype('float') / cm.sum(axis=1)[:, np.newaxis]
    plot_confusion_matrix(cm_normalized, title + ' Normalized')
    
    
    
    
    
def predict(classifier,Y,X):
    predictions = classifier.predict(Y)
    target = X
    evaluate_prediction(predictions, target)

y_score = []
y = label_binarize(Y, classes=['1','2','3'])
n_classes = y.shape[1]


X_train, X_test, y_train, y_test = train_test_split(train_data_features, y, test_size=.5,
                                                    random_state=0)
for model in spisok:
    classifier = OneVsRestClassifier(model)
    y_score.append( classifier.fit(X_train, y_train).predict_proba(X_test))


mmm = n_classes
classificator = ['ExtraTreesClassifier','RandomForestClassifier','LogisticRegression','XGBoost']
fpr = dict()
tpr = dict()
roc_auc = dict()
for j in range(len(y_score)):
    for i in range(n_classes):
        fpr[i+mmm*j], tpr[i+mmm*j], _ = roc_curve(y_test[:, i], y_score[j][:, i])
        roc_auc[i+mmm*j] = auc(fpr[i+mmm*j], tpr[i+mmm*j])

plt.figure()
lw = 2
colors = cycle(['aqua', 'darkorange', 'cornflowerblue'])
for i in range(n_classes):
        
    for j,color in zip(range(len(y_score)), colors):
        plt.plot(fpr[i+mmm*j], tpr[i+mmm*j], color=color, lw=lw,
                    label='class {0}  classificator: {1} (area = {2:0.2f})'
                    ''.format(i+1,classificator[j], roc_auc[i+mmm*j]))

    plt.plot([0, 1], [0, 1], 'k--', lw=lw)
    plt.xlim([0.0, 1.0])
    plt.ylim([0.0, 1.05])
    plt.xlabel('False Positive Rate')
    plt.ylabel('True Positive Rate')
    plt.title('An extension of Receiver operating characteristic to one-vs-rest multi-class')
    plt.legend(loc="lower right")
    plt.show()

def Word2Vec_transform(w2v, X):
        return np.array([
            np.mean([w2v[w] for w in f_tokenizer(words) if w in w2v.vocab] 
                    or [np.zeros(w2v.vector_size)], axis=0)
            for words in X
        ])

def remove_stop_words_and_tokenize(s):
    b = pd.read_excel('stop_words.xlsx')
    stop_words = [b['stop_words'][q] for q in range(0,b.shape[0])]
    morph = pymorphy2.MorphAnalyzer()
    f = ""
    punct = ['.',',',' ','"','!','(',')','?','+', '*', '-',':', ';', '?', '[', ']', '_','#','/']
    for r in punct:
        s = s.replace(r,' ')
    words = s.split(' ')
    for word in words:
        m = morph.parse(word)
        word = m[0]
        if word.tag.POS   in ('NOUN','ADJF'):
             if word.normal_form not in stop_words:
                        f = f + " " + word.normal_form+'_'+word.tag.POS
    return f

def NN_classificator(dense = 128,dropout = 0.3):
    model = Sequential()
    model.add(Dense(dense, input_dim=(Xtrain_NN.shape[1])))
    model.add(Activation('relu'))
    model.add(Dropout(dropout))
    model.add(Dense(dense- 30, input_dim=(Xtrain_NN.shape[1])))
    model.add(Activation('tanh'))
    model.add(Dropout(dropout))
    model.add(Dense(3))
    model.add(Activation('sigmoid'))
    model.compile(loss='binary_crossentropy',
                  optimizer='adam',
                  metrics=['accuracy'])
    return model
